            "bold": true
          },
          {
            "text": "\n\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0The Hanifi Rohingya script is cursive (joined) and written right-to-left (RTL). The change in shape is necessary to create a continuous, flowing line of script:\n\nJoining: When a character connects to the next, a small \"tail\" or connecting line extends from the body of the letter.\n\nCutting Off: When a character is at the end of a joining sequence (the final form), the connecting tail is cut off, and the letter often reverts to its full, independent shape for the termination."
