        "content": "\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0Saakin means when one alphabet 'catches' another alphabet and the sound does not start again from the last alphabet. This is called Saakin. Saakin can be written in the middle or at the end of a word. Saakin cannot be written at the beginning of a word. In Rohingya, Saakin can be used continuously with two or more alphabets in the same word."
